Special Needs Education Tracker (SNET) is a web app that helps teachers, therapists, and parents work together to support
students with special educational needs.
It gives everyone one place to track each student's learning goals, therapy sessions, and day-to-day progress 
so nothing falls through the cracks. Instead of juggling paperwork or scattered notes, you get a clear picture of how each
child is doing and what they need next. Different people like teachers, parents, specialists can log in and see 
what's relevant to them, get updates, and stay in sync. Progress is easy to follow through simple visuals, and data can
be exported whenever needed. The goal is straightforward: make it easier for the people who care for these students to 
stay informed, work together, and make better decisions for each child.
